  "body": "The kubelet restarts containers when a liveness probe fails, but the events don't show this. This makes it hard to debug cases with bad liveness probes because it will appear like the container is crashing, docker logs won't show anything really wrong with the container, but the kubelet will keep restarting it. \n\nMy events from a pod with a bad liveness probe:\n\n```\n  Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:08:30 -0700   Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:08:30 -0700 1   {kubelet 127.0.0.1} spec.containers{nginx}          killing     Killing 0b7743acd1a5f54aeccf4fe16c8cfbaa5e935a541c2fca59150cc250f7035d4e\n  Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:08:31 -0700   Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:08:31 -0700 1   {kubelet 127.0.0.1} spec.containers{nginx}          created     Created with docker id 39e349fd00c1cbcbb25e588e29e70e2c12b2e7b9a8020e02fbe462ae9fa61ea1\n  Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:08:31 -0700   Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:08:31 -0700 1   {kubelet 127.0.0.1} spec.containers{nginx}          started     Started with docker id 39e349fd00c1cbcbb25e588e29e70e2c12b2e7b9a8020e02fbe462ae9fa61ea1\n  Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:09:00 -0700   Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:09:00 -0700 1   {kubelet 127.0.0.1} spec.containers{nginx}          killing     Killing 39e349fd00c1cbcbb25e588e29e70e2c12b2e7b9a8020e02fbe462ae9fa61ea1\n  Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:09:00 -0700   Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:09:00 -0700 1   {kubelet 127.0.0.1} spec.containers{nginx}          created     Created with docker id 9b2a0596d1c9a0badf0ac07e5a2d4d74e71e2654177be26217e5a376a8062ca4\n  Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:09:00 -0700   Tue, 07 Apr 2015 12:09:00 -0700 1   {kubelet 127.0.0.1} spec.containers{nginx}          started     Started with docker id 9b2a0596d1c9a0badf0ac07e5a2d4d74e71e2654177be26217e5a376a8062ca4\n\n```\n\nI would find it easier if there was a reason in there like: the probe on ip:port/url failed\n",
